{"type":"message","id":"b049efb1","parentId":"60c4f36a","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:09:11.026Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540c9093bcb0c4f25e58895b1c5\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 04:09 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b540c9093bcb0c4f25e58895b1c5]\nou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2: 你现在是docker 部署 有办法让你管理其他docker 容器的方案吗"}],"timestamp":1773374951024}}
{"type":"message","id":"75e2821e","parentId":"b049efb1","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:09:58.885Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 有，而且方案不止一种。\n\n最直接的结论：**可以让现在这个跑在 Docker 里的我去管理别的 Docker 容器**，但本质上得给我一条能碰到 Docker daemon 的路。常见方案从“最方便”到“更稳妥”大概是这几种：\n\n### 1）挂宿主机的 Docker socket\n最常见：\n\n- 把宿主机的 `/var/run/docker.sock` 挂进我这个容器\n- 容器里再装 `docker` CLI，或者直接用能调用 Docker API 的工具\n\n这样我就能直接执行类似：\n\n- `docker ps`\n- `docker logs xxx`\n- `docker restart xxx`\n- `docker exec -it xxx ...`\n\n#### 优点\n- 最简单\n- 本机容器全都能管\n- 适合家里服务器 / 自己的机器\n\n#### 风险\n- **权限非常大**\n- 谁能用到这个 socket，基本就等于谁拿到了宿主机 root 级别控制权\n\n所以如果你走这条路，默认要把它当成“高权限模式”。\n\n---\n\n### 2）连远程 Docker daemon\n不是挂本机 socket，而是让我连别的机器上的 Docker：\n\n- 开 Docker Remote API\n- 用 TLS 证书保护\n- 或者走 SSH context\n\n比如：\n- `DOCKER_HOST=tcp://xxx:2376`\n- 或者 `docker context use remote-prod`\n\n#### 优点\n- 可以跨机器管理\n- 不一定非得碰宿主机本地 socket\n\n#### 缺点\n- 配置比 socket 麻烦\n- 远程 API 如果配不好，风险也很大\n\n---\n\n### 3）用 Portainer / Yacht / 1Panel 这类中间层\n也就是不让我直接碰 Docker daemon，而是：\n\n- 你部署一个容器管理面板\n- 我通过浏览器去操作它\n- 或者调用它的 API\n\n#### 优点\n- 权限更好收敛\n- UI 清楚\n- 审计、用户权限、栈管理更舒服\n\n#### 缺点\n- 比直接 `docker` 多一层\n- 有些高级操作没 CLI 灵活\n\n如果你想要“能管理，但别给太粗暴的宿主权限”，这类方案其实挺合适。\n\n---\n\n### 4）只给特定自动化能力\n如果你不想让我“全权管 Docker”，还可以做成更收敛的形式：\n\n- 写几个宿主机脚本  \n  比如：\n  - `restart-app.sh`\n  - `backup-db.sh`\n  - `show-logs.sh`\n- 我只被允许调用这些脚本\n- 或者通过 `docker compose` 只管某一个目录下的服务\n\n#### 优点\n- 最安全\n- 能把我能做的事情限制死\n\n#### 缺点\n- 灵活性差一点\n- 每个动作都要先设计\n\n如果你担心安全，我其实更推荐这个思路。\n\n---\n\n## 如果你的目标是“让我真的帮你管容器”\n我会建议分成三档：\n\n### A. 省事版\n给我 Docker socket：\n\n- 挂载 `/var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock`\n- 容器里可用 `docker` 命令\n\n适合：\n- 自己家里的机器\n- 你完全信任我和这套环境\n\n---\n\n### B. 折中版\n给我一个管理面板：\n\n- Portainer\n- 我通过 browser 工具去点\n- 或者走它的 API\n\n适合：\n- 想看得见、管得住\n- 不想把 socket 直接裸给我\n\n---\n\n### C. 安全版\n只开放白名单操作：\n\n- 固定脚本\n- 固定 compose 项目\n- 固定容器名\n- 只允许 restart / logs / status 之类动作\n\n适合：\n- 线上环境\n- 多服务机器\n- 你只想让我“运维助手化”，不是“宿主机管理员化”\n\n---\n\n## 我这里的现实限制\n就算理论上能管，**前提还是你给我访问通道**。  \n不然我现在在容器里，看不见宿主机 Docker daemon，就只能“告诉你怎么做”，不能真动手。\n\n换句话说，得满足至少一个条件：\n\n- 能访问宿主机 `/var/run/docker.sock`\n- 或者能访问远程 Docker API / SSH\n- 或者能操作一个容器管理面板\n- 或者能调用你预先做好的宿主机脚本\n\n---\n\n## 我建议你怎么选\n如果是你自己机器，想让我帮你：\n\n### 最推荐\n**“白名单脚本 + 少量必要权限”**\n\n例如只做这些能力：\n- 看容器状态\n- 看日志\n- 重启指定容器\n- 拉起/停止某个 compose 项目\n- 备份数据库\n\n这样比直接全开 socket 稳很多。\n\n### 如果你追求简单\n**直接挂 docker.sock**\n\n但要默认接受这个事实：\n> 这基本等于把宿主机控制权交出来一大块。\n\n---\n\n## 你要的话，我可以下一步直接帮你设计一套\n我可以按你的环境给你出具体方案，比如：\n\n1. **最省事的 docker-compose 改法**\n2. **更安全的“脚本代理”方案**\n3. **Portainer 方案**\n4. **远程多机器 Docker 管理方案**\n\n如果你愿意，我下一条可以直接给你一份：\n\n- 你当前 OpenClaw 容器的 `docker-compose.yml` 修改示例\n- 或者一套“只允许我管理指定容器”的安全方案\n\n你回我一句：\n\n- **“给我最简单方案”**\n- 或者 **“给我安全一点的方案”**\n\n我就直接写配置。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":10794,"output":1733,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15087,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773374951025}}
{"type":"message","id":"bc235e42","parentId":"75e2821e","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:11:09.829Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b540cab02aca0c4242cf851e624b\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Fri 2026-03-13 04:11 UTC\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2\"\n}\n```\n\n[message_id: om_x100b540cab02aca0c4242cf851e624b]\nou_89d790689d0059dfcc29b83ffac2dab2: 那docker 数据 目录 挂载 如何控制呢"}],"timestamp":1773375069828}}
{"type":"message","id":"97dcf62c","parentId":"bc235e42","timestamp":"2026-03-13T04:12:03.066Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Searching for concise answers**\n\nI see the user is asking a general question, and it looks like I might not need any tools for this. Since there's no prior work to reference, I can focus on the current topic. It might be helpful to mention bind mounts to clarify, but I need to keep it concise and offer the answer in Chinese as they requested. So, I'll make sure I'm clear and straightforward!\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 这个要分开看：**“管容器”** 和 **“管数据目录”** 其实是两层权限。\n\n如果你把 Docker socket 给我了，**理论上我就能新建/修改容器挂载**，那等于我也能碰很多宿主机目录。  \n所以数据目录控制的关键，不是“挂不挂”，而是**你打算把多大的宿主机文件系统暴露给 Docker 这层能力**。\n\n---\n\n## 先说结论\n\n### 最危险的情况\n如果给了我 Docker socket，而且不做限制，那我可以创建这种容器：\n\n- 挂 `/`\n- 挂 `/home`\n- 挂 `/etc`\n- 挂任意业务数据目录\n\n这基本就不是“管容器”了，是**间接管宿主机文件系统**。\n\n---\n\n## 想控制数据目录，常见有 4 种思路\n\n# 1）只允许管理“已有容器”，不允许新建容器\n这是最重要的一层。\n\n比如你只让我做：\n\n- `docker ps`\n- `docker logs`\n- `docker restart`\n- `docker stop/start`\n\n**不允许：**\n- `docker run`\n- `docker create`\n- `docker compose up`（新建或重建时可能改挂载）\n- `docker update` / 改 volume 配置\n\n### 好处\n这样我最多只能碰**现有容器已经挂进去的数据**，没法临时再去挂新的宿主机目录。\n\n### 适合\n- 你只是想让我帮忙运维\n- 看状态、看日志、重启服务\n\n---\n\n# 2）把我能操作的范围限制到某个 compose 项目\n比如只允许我管理：\n\n- `/opt/apps/blog/docker-compose.yml`\n- `/opt/apps/memos/docker-compose.yml`\n\n而这些 compose 文件里的挂载是你预先写死的，比如：\n\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - /srv/blog/data:/app/data\n  - /srv/blog/config:/app/config\n```\n\n我只能执行：\n\n- `docker compose -f /opt/apps/blog/docker-compose.yml ps`\n- `docker compose -f /opt/apps/blog/docker-compose.yml restart`\n- `docker compose -f /opt/apps/blog/docker-compose.yml up -d`\n\n但**不能改这个 yml**，也不能跑别的 compose 文件。\n\n### 好处\n你把挂载白名单提前固定住了。\n\n### 风险\n如果我还能编辑这个 compose 文件，那限制就没意义了。  \n所以最好：\n- compose 文件目录只读\n- 或者我根本不直接碰文件，只能调用包装脚本\n\n---\n\n# 3）用“包装脚本”做白名单\n这个是我最推荐的。\n\n你在宿主机放几个脚本，比如：\n\n### 查看状态\n```bash\n/usr/local/bin/oc-docker-status\n```\n\n### 重启指定服务\n```bash\n/usr/local/bin/oc-restart-blog\n```\n\n### 查看日志\n```bash\n/usr/local/bin/oc-logs-blog\n```\n\n脚本内部把路径和容器名写死，比如：\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\ndocker compose -f /opt/apps/blog/docker-compose.yml restart\n```\n\n或者：\n\n```bash\n#!/usr/bin/env bash\ndocker logs --tail=200 blog-app\n```\n\n### 好处\n我根本不知道、也碰不到其他目录。  \n我只是在用你给我的几个按钮。\n\n### 这是控制数据目录最稳的方式\n因为：\n- 挂载目录由你预定义\n- 我不能自己临时加 `/srv/mysql`、`/home`、`/etc`\n- 也不能新建一个恶意容器去扫盘\n\n---\n\n# 4）尽量用 named volume，而不是宿主机任意 bind mount\n比如不要老是这样：\n\n```yaml\n- /home/xxx/some/random/path:/data\n```\n\n更可控的是：\n\n```yaml\nvolumes:\n  - app_data:/data\n```\n\n由 Docker 自己管理 volume。\n\n### 好处\n- 不直接暴露宿主机任意目录\n- 结构更统一\n- 备份迁移更方便\n\n### 缺点\n- 有时候你想手动进宿主机看文件，没 bind mount 那么直观\n\n### 折中\n对真正需要人工查看的配置目录用 bind mount，  \n对业务数据尽量用 named volume。\n\n---\n\n## 如果你问的是：挂载目录本身怎么“限制访问”\n这里也有几层：\n\n### A. 宿主机目录权限\n比如：\n\n- 专门建 `/srv/containers/blog`\n- 用单独用户 ownership\n- 权限设成最小\n\n但要注意：  \n**只要有人能完全控制 Docker daemon，宿主机 chmod 这类权限意义会被削弱很多。**\n\n因为 Docker 本身就是高权限入口。\n\n所以：\n> **文件权限不是第一道防线，真正的防线是别把 Docker daemon 的完全控制权放开。**\n\n---\n\n### B. 挂载时只读\n有些目录可以只读挂进去：\n\n```yaml\n- /srv/blog/config:/app/config:ro\n```\n\n这样容器内只能读，不能写。\n\n适合：\n- 配置文件\n- 静态资源\n- 模板目录\n\n不适合：\n- 数据库数据目录\n- 上传目录\n- 缓存目录\n\n---\n\n### C. 拆分目录\n不要一个大目录全挂。  \n比如别这样：\n\n```yaml\n- /srv/blog:/app\n```\n\n更好是拆成：\n\n```yaml\n- /srv/blog/config:/app/config:ro\n- /srv/blog/uploads:/app/uploads\n- /srv/blog/data:/app/data\n```\n\n### 好处\n每块权限清楚很多：\n- config 只读\n- uploads 可写\n- data 可写\n- 其他宿主机内容不暴露\n\n---\n\n## 如果你的目标是“我能帮你，但别乱碰数据”\n我建议你用这个组合：\n\n### 推荐组合\n1. **不给我直接随便 run 容器的能力**\n2. **只允许我调用固定脚本**\n3. **每个业务的挂载目录提前写死**\n4. **配置目录尽量只读**\n5. **数据目录独立到 `/srv/<app>/...`**\n6. **能用 named volume 的地方尽量用 named volume**\n\n---\n\n## 一个比较稳的示例\n\n### 宿主机目录\n```bash\n/srv/memos/config\n/srv/memos/data\n/srv/memos/uploads\n/opt/apps/memos/docker-compose.yml\n```\n\n### compose\n```yaml\nservices:\n  memos:\n    image: neosmemo/memos:stable\n    volumes:\n      - /srv/memos/config:/var/opt/memos/config:ro\n      - /srv/memos/data:/var/opt/memos/data\n      - /srv/memos/uploads:/var/opt/memos/uploads\n```\n\n### 只给我这些脚本\n```bash\n/usr/local/bin/oc-memos-status\n/usr/local/bin/oc-memos-restart\n/usr/local/bin/oc-memos-logs\n/usr/local/bin/oc-memos-up\n```\n\n我就只能围着这个应用打转，碰不到别的目录。\n\n---\n\n## 一句话判断标准\n\n如果你发现“给了我这个能力后，我理论上可以把 `/` 或 `/home` 挂进新容器”，  \n那说明**你的控制还不够收敛**。\n\n---\n\n## 你现在最该选哪种\n### 如果你是家里自己玩\n可以稍微放松一点，但也建议至少：\n- 固定 compose 项目\n- 不开放任意 `docker run`\n\n### 如果是生产环境\n直接上：\n- **脚本白名单**\n- **固定 compose**\n- **少量读日志/重启能力**\n- **不要开放任意新建容器**\n\n---\n\n如果你愿意，我下一条可以直接给你两份可落地的东西：\n\n1. **“最简单版”**：让 OpenClaw 能管理指定 compose 项目  \n2. **“更安全版”**：只开放几个脚本，严格限制数据目录\n\n你回我一句 **“给我安全版示例”**，我直接把目录结构、compose、脚本范例一起写给你。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1734,"output":1908,"cacheRead":13184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16826,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773375069828}}
{"type":"message","id":"877f2457","parentId":"97dcf62c","timestamp":"2026-03-13T13:59:02.951Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Fri 2026-03-13 21:59 GMT+8] 根据 https://skillhub-1388575217.cos.ap-guangzhou.myqcloud.com/install/skillhub.md 安装 Skillhub商店，但是只安装CLI。"}],"timestamp":1773410342948}}
{"type":"message","id":"7061233f","parentId":"877f2457","timestamp":"2026-03-13T13:59:18.938Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_KVtYXuF9GJ8LXh5VgNeAhuuT","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/app/skills/clawhub/SKILL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_HMgCHURYkXLxurIyfkHHq4Tt","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Xib20FgXJyvGVkzmqgd9ttgh","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1JTOTYO79RAOFTG95RQrQQRN","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-13.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_BZ7qO7leEcUzCXG62FxUSNEW","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-03-12.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oiSA1Lml6O2PHvfETYP6HCZG","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":15413,"output":579,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18552,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773410342950}}
{"type":"message","id":"c31170c0","parentId":"7061233f","timestamp":"2026-03-13T13:59:18.951Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KVtYXuF9GJ8LXh5VgNeAhuuT","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: clawhub\ndescription: Use the ClawHub CLI to search, install, update, and publish agent skills from clawhub.com. Use when you need to fetch new skills on the fly, sync installed skills to latest or a specific version, or publish new/updated skill folders with the npm-installed clawhub CLI.\nmetadata:\n  {\n    \"openclaw\":\n      {\n        \"requires\": { \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"] },\n        \"install\":\n          [\n            {\n              \"id\": \"node\",\n              \"kind\": \"node\",\n              \"package\": \"clawhub\",\n              \"bins\": [\"clawhub\"],\n              \"label\": \"Install ClawHub CLI (npm)\",\n            },\n          ],\n      },\n  }\n---\n\n# ClawHub CLI\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nnpm i -g clawhub\n```\n\nAuth (publish)\n\n```bash\nclawhub login\nclawhub whoami\n```\n\nSearch\n\n```bash\nclawhub search \"postgres backups\"\n```\n\nInstall\n\n```bash\nclawhub install my-skill\nclawhub install my-skill --version 1.2.3\n```\n\nUpdate (hash-based match + upgrade)\n\n```bash\nclawhub update my-skill\nclawhub update my-skill --version 1.2.3\nclawhub update --all\nclawhub update my-skill --force\nclawhub update --all --no-input --force\n```\n\nList\n\n```bash\nclawhub list\n```\n\nPublish\n\n```bash\nclawhub publish ./my-skill --slug my-skill --name \"My Skill\" --version 1.2.0 --changelog \"Fixes + docs\"\n```\n\nNotes\n\n- Default registry: https://clawhub.com (override with CLAWHUB_REGISTRY or --registry)\n- Default workdir: cwd (falls back to OpenClaw workspace); install dir: ./skills (override with --workdir / --dir / CLAWHUB_WORKDIR)\n- Update command hashes local files, resolves matching version, and upgrades to latest unless --version is set\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773410358949}}
{"type":"message","id":"218bdc87","parentId":"c31170c0","timestamp":"2026-03-13T13:59:18.959Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_HMgCHURYkXLxurIyfkHHq4Tt","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773410358958}}
