{"type":"message","id":"97eb8008","parentId":"ebe8c131","timestamp":"2026-03-13T14:12:52.306Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Inspecting the directory**\n\nI need to inspect the /opt/apps directory. It seems like I don’t need any specific reading skills; just a basic reading should be enough. I plan to execute a command like `ls -la` to find the compose files. Since the user asked me to check this directory, I'll do that and maybe provide a brief narration of what I'm doing. I might need to confirm whether I have permission to read the local files.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"我先看看 `/opt/apps` 下面有什么项目和 compose 文件。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9v5ovEBjXNT65ZEDT36txP0e","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"set -e\nif [ -d /opt/apps ]; then\n  echo '== /opt/apps =='\n  ls -la /opt/apps\n  echo\n  echo '== depth 2 files named compose =='\n  find /opt/apps -maxdepth 2 \\( -name 'docker-compose.yml' -o -name 'docker-compose.yaml' -o -name 'compose.yml' -o -name 'compose.yaml' \\) -print | sort\nelse\n  echo '/opt/apps does not exist'\nfi","workdir":"/home/node/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":60}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":2219,"output":327,"cacheRead":20480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23026,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773411161894}}
